course_description: This course covers the fundamentals of time series analysis in both the natural and social sciences, utilizing analytical, statistical, and numerical approaches. We will focus on the application of these methods to complex, real world data from medicine, economics, geology, and other fields.
prerequisites: QTM 220 or equivalent transfer credit as prerequisite.
